line_2: A Man with half an Eye may see,
Turn We this Globe; and let Us see,

line_1: But not our passions only disagree,
line_2: In taste is found as great variety:

line_1: Some Persons with themselves so disagree,
line_2: They're fix'd to nothing but Inconstancy;

line_1: But then as often too they disagree,
line_2: Which proves the soul's superior progeny.

line_1: Tho' about ways and means they may all disagree;
line_2: Dominion and wealth are the aim of all three,

line_1: Why then, dear Smith, since Doctors disagree,
line_2: Their notions are not oracles to me:

line_1: My vows and wishes wildly disagree,
line_2: And grace itself mistakes my God for thee.
